      • setFailOnFlowControlLimits

        public Publisher.Builder setFailOnFlowControlLimits(boolean fail)
        Whether to fail publish when reaching any of the flow control limits, with either a FlowController.MaxOutstandingRequestBytesReachedException or FlowController.MaxOutstandingElementCountReachedException as appropriate.

        If set to false, then publish operations will block the current thread until the outstanding requests go under the limits.
